\series bold 
Predicting Interaction Forces between Objects
\series default 
 
\layout Standard

We recently focused our attention on the change in momentum that an object
 undergoes when it experiences a force that is extended over time (even
 if that time is very short!).
 Since interactions like collisions and explosions never involve just one
 object, we would like to turn our attention to the mutual forces of interaction
 between two or more objects.
 As usual, you will be asked to make some predictions about interaction
 forces and then be given the opportunity to test these predictions.
 
\layout Standard


